OpenBSD Network Syscalls

This module provides OpenBSD-specific network syscall implementations,
including BSD sockets and OpenBSD security-focused networking features.

Key features and capabilities:
- BSD socket operations
- TCP/UDP networking
- Raw sockets (pledge-restricted)
- Routing sockets
- Network interface management
- Packet filter (pf) integration
- BPF support
- Network statistics
- IPsec integration
- IPv6 support
- Network isolation
- Socket splicing
- Network pledges
- Secure networking
- Traffic shaping
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../../compiler/backend/syscalls/platforms/openbsd_x64" as OpenBSDPlatform
Import "../../../../../../../compiler/backend/syscalls/platforms/platform_interface" as PlatformInterface
